# Dialog Window Standards

## Core

- Build dialogs with `CustomDialog` from `@/components/ui/custom-dialog`.
- Do not use raw Radix or HTML dialog primitives in feature code when `CustomDialog` can be used.
- Every dialog must show a visible header and a visible footer.
- All global actions (Cancel, Save, Submit, Delete, Confirm, Next, Previous, etc.) belong in the **footer** only.
- Do not put primary or secondary global actions in the dialog body.
- Footer buttons use natural width from their label; do not use `w-full` or `flex-1` on footer buttons unless the feature explicitly requires it.

## Footer layout

- Place Cancel and the primary action on one row, **right-aligned**, using `flex items-center justify-end gap-2` (inner row; `CustomDialog` already outer-aligns the footer on larger breakpoints).
- **Cancel:** `Button` with `variant="outline"`, `size="default"`, and `className` including `h-10 px-4 border-[var(--glass-border)] text-foreground hover:bg-accent`.
- **Primary:** `Button` with `variant="accent"` and `size="default"`; label matches the action (Save, Create, Submit, etc.).
- **Primary icon:** For create/save/submit actions that persist data, put the Lucide `Save` icon before the label: `className="w-4 h-4 mr-2"`. For destructive confirm, use an icon that matches the action (e.g. `Trash2`) with the same size and `mr-2`. Other actions may use icons only when they clarify the action.

## Padding (match `CustomDialog`)

- Do not add extra outer padding that fights the shell; use `noContentPadding` only when the body intentionally controls its own full-bleed layout.
- Default shell: header uses `p-6 pb-4` and a bottom border; body uses `p-6` when the standard header is shown; footer uses `px-6 py-3` and `border-t border-[var(--glass-border)]`.
- Inside the body, use vertical spacing utilities (`space-y-*`) instead of stacking conflicting `p-*` on nested wrappers.

## Theme

- Use shared tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-[var(--glass-border)]`, and accent-aware variants where applicable.
- Keep light/dark behavior consistent with the rest of the app.

## Reuse and structure

- Use shared controls from `@/components/ui` for inputs, buttons, and labels.
- Factor repeated dialog sections into small shared components when the same pattern repeats.
- Prefer one dialog per folder with a clear name; avoid one huge file with unrelated dialogs.

## Wizard dialogs

- Multi-step flows must show a visible **step progress bar** only (no second progress UI such as a numeric stepper alongside it).
- Implement each step as its own component (not one long inline block).
- Progress bar width is `w-1/2` of the dialog content area (`w-1/2`), centered (`mx-auto` or equivalent).
- Align the bar with the active step and theme accents.

## Tabbed dialogs

- Implement each tab as its own component (not one long inline tab block).
- Put tab-scoped controls (Add, Edit selected, Delete selected) in the tab body when they only affect that tabâ€™s content.
- Global actions stay in the footer; tab actions must not replace required footer actions.
- For tab list rows, use a kebab menu (`MoreVertical`) for row actions; include Edit/Delete (and other row actions as needed) with theme/accent styling.
